[SAM v1 — The BAM Format Specification] Most length and count fields described as  uint32\_t have additional constraints on their range:
$ l\_text < 2^31$ due to implementation limits;
$ n\_ref < 2^31$ because  refID and  next\_refID are signed;
$ l\_ref < 2^31$ because  tlen is signed;
those marked ``limited'' are limited by available memory and the practical size of the data represented well before they are limited by, e.g., Java's signed 32-bit integer maximum array size.

